class Solution {
    public int hammingDistance(int x, int y) {
        int diff = x ^ y;
        int count = 0;
        while (diff != 0) {
            count += diff & 1;
            diff >>= 1;
        }
        return count;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log(max(x, y)))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution utilizes the bitwise XOR operator to find the differences between the bits of the two integers. It then iterates through the resulting bits, counting the number of set bits, which represents the Hamming distance. This approach leverages the efficient bitwise operations and has a time complexity proportional to the number of bits in the integers, making it highly efficient.

